    <item>
      <title>The 15-minute visualiser is out now. It captures all nine films, created as the ...</title>
      <link>https://www.instagram.com/p/DLW4JI5hlMQ/</link>
      <description><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DLW4JI5hlMQ/"><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.75761-15/511323732_18513742819020866_9074755318377994988_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_s640x640_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=105&amp;ig_cache_key=MzY2MzM2MjI2NTU0NzQyODYyNA%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjk3N3gxNzM4LnNkci5DMyJ9&amp;_nc_ohc=WcrAvzW5B7YQ7kNvwHjDYrP&amp;_nc_oc=AdoyZtwhZ2ubkQtp7AiKgkyg4756NmVt0XNsRZuhhrZWplDL9ijhJG9KS7lmV5wNZt4&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=lX6ENCWtvdvjNx673OSU_Q&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfzSCWsCFcm16wPK0730gef1ytB2Ie_swYBqozRFA-ForA&amp;oe=69CA080D" alt="Video-thumbnail fra @frederikvalentin" /></a></p><p><strong>🎬 Video</strong></p><p><strong>@frederikvalentin</strong></p><p>The 15-minute visualiser is out now.<br/>
<br/>
It captures all nine films, created as the visual side to the tracks from the album ROCK N ROLL WILL NEVER DIE.<br/>
<br/>
Shot across two days, the camera remained quietly observant as new, unplanned sounds and fragments of music emerged — small improvisations, field recordings, gestures toward future compositions. <br/>
Some of those have now been released as part of the Deluxe version of the album, which has been retitled: <br/>
DEDICATED TO MY FATHER WHO FOUGHT AND DEFEATED 1 MILLION YEARS OF HATE AND VIOLENCE.<br/>
<br/>
The tracks PLAY, MUSIC, SPACE, and OPENING contain echoes of that process — audio debris and memory residue, captured live during the making of the visual piece.<br/>
<br/>
It is a document of time passing, of music in its unscripted state. A reflection on legacy, place, and the way sound lives alongside image, sometimes without asking.<br/>
<br/>
Thank you for engaging with this piece. <br/>
Video by Frederik Valentin &amp; Mads Junker<br/>
